<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Frustule shape is cylindrical to approximately octagonal (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM (A-D, H) and LM (E-G) images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city: A-G Melosira subglobosa (A, F girdle views, B-E, G, valve views) H Melosira varians, partial valve view and girdle view of complete frustule. Scale bars: 10 μm (A-C, E-H); 20 μm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545734" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">2A, F</figureCitation>
). Valve 12.5-26 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter, mantle height 3.1-8.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Valve face nearly octagonal with flat tops (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM (A-D, H) and LM (E-G) images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city: A-G Melosira subglobosa (A, F girdle views, B-E, G, valve views) H Melosira varians, partial valve view and girdle view of complete frustule. Scale bars: 10 μm (A-C, E-H); 20 μm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545734" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">2B-E, G</figureCitation>
). Girdle with puncta forming straight and transverse rows 32-56 in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
